                   <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-purple-500" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 15a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h14a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z"/></svg>
                   BGP Communities
                 </h3>
                 <div class="space-y-4 text-[11px] text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                   <p>
                     Metadata "tags" attached to routes that signal instructions to upstream peers. Standardized via <a href="https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc1997" target="_blank" class="text-indigo-600 dark:text-cyan-400 underline decoration-dotted">RFC 1997</a> and <a href="https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc4360" target="_blank" class="text-indigo-600 dark:text-cyan-400 underline decoration-dotted">RFC 4360</a>. Important note: most community semantics are <strong>operator-defined</strong> and not universal.
                   </p>
                   <ul class="space-y-3 list-disc pl-4">
                     <li>
                       <strong>Blackholing:</strong> Used for DDoS mitigation. 
                       <span class="block opacity-70 mt-0.5 italic">Example: <code class="bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 px-1 rounded">65535:666</code> (Standardized RTBH)</span>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                       <strong>Traffic Steering:</strong> Influencing path priority. 
                       <span class="block opacity-70 mt-0.5 italic">Example: <code class="bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 px-1 rounded">ASN:70</code> (Common convention to Set Local-Pref 70, but varies per ISP)</span>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                       <strong>Scoping:</strong> Preventing regional leakage. 
                       <span class="block opacity-70 mt-0.5 italic">Example: <code class="bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 px-1 rounded">NO_EXPORT</code> (Well-known RFC 1997)</span>
                     </li>
                   </ul>
                 </div>
              </div>

            </div>
